	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100996969134402><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=6292&mid=100996969134402>this stuff rocks(when imbued that is)</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=6292&mid=100996969134402#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=130284><span id=Scholar>shizuka</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>17 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Jan 2nd 6:08 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>nothing personal to all of you who like to spout off about things before looking into them. but a full set of this stuff will give u 60 str and wieghs only 26.6 stone! that means you get an extra 33.4 wt capacity just by wearing this stuff, thats amazing for my erudite cleric that started with a 70 str. the prexus imbued also gives 29 wis, 8 int, over 100 hp, over 150 mana, around 70 to svp, almost 40 dex, and almost 20 to agi! a full set will grant you a 149 ac bonus, which isn't bad at all for a class that barely fights by the time they can get this stuff. now for the fashion consious players, this stuff is some of the coolest things an erudite can wear, just by looks alone, plus its rather rare to see someone in a full set running around(got to love individuality ;p). imho its well worth the day or so to camp the terrorantula. despite its rare spawn rate, it will always drop at least 1 and up to 5 silks and almost always at least 3 on average. its a lvl 37-40, 60 ft tall spider with a desent amount of health and stackable poison and it can spawn a few times an hr or as long as every few hrs. but i know several ppl that have solo'd it with easy in there mid-40's which means with a decent group u can do this around 35-40 to pass the time while helpin the others in your group who may be questing jboots(not to mention the named skellie that drops the charred bone chios that r needed for that sweet cleric helm quest, hehe). the imbued versions actually triv sooner than the normal stuff as well (around 120 for imbued and 170 for regular) so with a decent tailoring of around 150, you shouldn't fail to many times at this. plus even though i semi twink most of my new chrs, i believe you should have to wait for some of the nice stuff and this is very definatly still quite nice into your 40's for a full set or even for those odd crap peices u still may be wearing and want to change out for somethin decent. the other two imbued versions r also rather decent, quelious gets 2 cha and svd to every piece and better hp bonuses on a few pieces, yet doesn't get much dex and a little less agi. then the cazic thule version gets about the same int bonus as the wis on the prexus version and only 8 wis, and also gets decent bonuses with all the physical stats while taking a negative 2 cha hit per piece, so with the wt/str bonus and half decent ac and all the other great bonuses, it's not to bad for those weak erudite sk's either. scough at this stuff all u want but this is what i'll b wearing till i can get the week off from work in my higher lvls to do plane raids for my final major equip up grades. ;D<br>&nbsp;<br>prices r in the eye of the holder and the coin purse of the buyer.<br>shizuka kage, dark elf chanter</td></tr>
